{"nodes": [{"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_document", "label": "Design", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_context", "label": "Context", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 1", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Current Ex support is finite and prompt-local. `src/ex.ts` parses explicit Ex command variants; `src/range.ts` owns finite range algebra; `src/buffer.ts` owns prompt-buffer edits; modal code owns side effects; `src/vim-editor.ts` renders the shared search/Ex/message workbench row. Archived changes already shipped regex pattern mode via `r`, address offsets, semicolon ranges, destination offsets, shared workbench history, and substitution preview/apply. `TODOS.md ## Ex Commands` is therefore part"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_goals_non_goals", "label": "Goals / Non-Goals", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 7", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "**Goals:** - Reconcile stale TODOs/docs with source-backed behavior before adding new Ex work."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_decisions", "label": "Decisions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 25", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "### 1. Treat TODO completion as cleanup plus bounded extensions Target seams: `TODOS.md`, `docs/features.md`, `openspec/specs/vim-ex-command-line/spec.md`, parser/tests."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_1_treat_todo_completion_as_cleanup_plus_bounded_extensions", "label": "1. Treat TODO completion as cleanup plus bounded extensions", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 27", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `TODOS.md`, `docs/features.md`, `openspec/specs/vim-ex-command-line/spec.md`, parser/tests. Decision: mark already-shipped TODOs complete only after tests/docs prove behavior exists. Do not reimplement regex substitution, offsets, semicolon ranges, or history. Fix stale docs that still list those capabilities as limitations."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_2_add_substitution_flags_as_an_explicit_typed_subset", "label": "2. Add substitution flags as an explicit typed subset", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 38", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/ex.ts`, substitution execution in modal/buffer helpers, `test/ex.test.ts`, `test/modal.test.ts`, `docs/features.md`. Decision: extend parsed substitutions with explicit booleans for safe flags:"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_3_store_semantic_last_substitution_for_repeat_commands", "label": "3. Store semantic last substitution for repeat commands", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 55", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/types.ts`, `src/ex.ts`, `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts`, substitution executor tests. Decision: add modal state for the last successfully applied substitution, separate from `exHistory`. Store parsed substitution semantics needed to repeat safely: pattern, replacement, matcher mode, flags, and original command text for diagnostics. Repeat commands (`:&` and `:&&`) resolve the current or explicit range, reuse stored semantics, and still use the existing preview/apply path "}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_4_add_ex_register_operands_through_existing_register_helpers", "label": "4. Add Ex register operands through existing register helpers", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 68", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/ex.ts`, `src/modal/registers.ts`, Ex line-command execution, `test/ex.test.ts`, `test/modal.test.ts`, `openspec/specs/vim-named-registers/spec.md`. Decision: parse one optional alphabetic register operand for `delete`, `yank`, and `put`:"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_5_use_a_bounded_command_line_editing_helper_not_a_nested_full_editor", "label": "5. Use a bounded command-line editing helper, not a nested full editor", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 86", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts`, `src/modal/types.ts`, command key helpers, modal tests. Decision: add cursor-aware editing to pending Ex state through a pure helper. `PendingExCommand` gains a cursor index. Printable input inserts at the cursor; Backspace/Delete remove around the cursor; Left/Right/Home/End and word-left/word-right/delete-word commands operate on the command string. History recall replaces the command and moves the cursor to the end. Any edit clears pending substit"}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_6_configure_reserved_workbench_rows_in_the_existing_ui_tree", "label": "6. Configure reserved workbench rows in the existing ui tree", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 97", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/types.ts`, `src/config.ts`, `src/vim-editor.ts`, render/config tests, `docs/settings.md`, `docs/features.md`. Decision: add `piVimMode.ui.workbench.reservedRows` as a bounded non-negative integer, default `0`. Active search/Ex/message workbench content still needs at least one row. Rendering reserves `max(activeWorkbenchRows, reservedRows)` rows below the prompt; blank reserved rows remain width-safe and keep prompt viewport height stable. v1 content remains single-row; extra "}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_7_extract_modal_handlers_before_adding_behavior_branches", "label": "7. Extract modal handlers before adding behavior branches", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 110", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Target seams: `src/modal/engine.ts`, `src/modal/normal.ts`, `src/modal/ex-command-line.ts`, tests. Decision: perform behavior-preserving extraction around Ex execution, normal command application, and visual input handling before adding new features. Keep pure helpers near their domain and avoid widening `VimEditor`. This is implementation structure, not a behavior capability."}, {"id": "2026_06_05_complete_ex_commands_todos_design_ref_src_ex_ts", "label": "ex.ts", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "openspec/changes/archive/2026-06-05-complete-ex-commands-todos/design.md", "source_location": "line 3", 